# Supabase Setup Walkthrough — GPA-S-LMS

## What Was Done

Applied **3 migrations** to the Supabase project **GPA-S-LMS** (`pistwngkqbfjgjtwmgee`, region: `ap-northeast-2`):

| Migration | Tables Created | Details |
|---|---|---|
| `create_core_library_tables` | 6 | [students](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#856-871), [books](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#884-898), `borrow_records`, [transactions](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#980-987), [promotion_history](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#1081-1096), [academic_years](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/database.py#1211-1222) + 5 performance indexes |
| `create_portal_tables` | 10 | [requests](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/Web-Extension/student_portal.py#95-119), `student_auth`, [notices](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#11752-11804), [deletion_requests](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/main.py#14500-14550), `user_settings`, `user_notifications`, `book_waitlist`, `access_logs`, [study_materials](file:///c:/Users/Yash/OneDrive/Desktop/GPA-S-LMS/LibraryApp/Web-Extension/student_portal.py#3287-3314), `book_ratings` |
| `disable_rls_for_direct_psycopg2_access` | — | Disabled RLS on all 16 tables |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> RLS was disabled because the app connects via **direct `psycopg2`** (not the Supabase JS SDK). RLS with no policies would block all queries.

### 🟡 Bug 8 — Overdue books show "On Time" due to wrong days parser (`Dashboard.jsx`)
**Fix:** Replaced `parseInt(book.days_msg?.replace(/\D/g, ''))` with a targeted regex `match(/^(\d+)\s*days?\s*left/i)`. Old code stripped all non-digits from strings like `"101 days late"` → `"101"`, which is > 3, so the status showed as `'normal'`. New code only extracts the "X days left" pattern; anything else (including overdue messages) defaults to 99 and relies on the primary `book.status === 'overdue'` guard.

